'''Zineddine Belaïd''' ({{langx|ar|زَيْن الدِّين بَلْعِيد}}; [[Berber languages|Tamazight]]: ⵣⵉⵏⴷⴷⵉⵏ ⴱⵍⵄⵉⴷ; born 20 March 1999) is an Algerian professional [[football player|footballer]] who plays as a [[centre-back]] for [[JS Kabylie]] and the [[Algeria national football team|Algeria national team]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.matchendirect.fr/joueur/zineddine-belaid.html|title=Zineddine Belaïd}}</ref>

==Club career==
On 31 May 2018, Zinedine Belaïd signed his first professional contract with [[NA Hussein Dey]] and played his first match at the professional level on 20 January 2019 in the [[2018–19 CAF Confederation Cup|CAF Confederation Cup]] against [[Al-Ahly SC (Benghazi)|Al-Ahly Benghazi]] of Libya. In his first season, Belaid only played three matches. In his second season Belaid became a key piece in the team and on 30 October 2019, Belaid scored the first goal in his football career against [[JS Saoura]] which led him to a 1–0 victory. On 11 October 2020, Belaïd signed a four-year contract with [[USM Alger]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dzfoot.com/2020/10/11/usma-zinnedine-belaid-va-signer-189857.php |title=USMA : Zineddine Belaid va signer |website=[[:fr:DZfoot|DZFoot.com]] |date=11 October 2020 |access-date=11 October 2020}}</ref> Belaïd became a key player in the team and got the captain's armband, Belaïd is in the sights of [[Al-Arabi SC (Qatar)|Al-Arabi SC]] winners of this season's [[2023 Emir of Qatar Cup|Emir of Qatar Cup]], The coach [[Younes Ali]] would already be delighted to see the native of the city of [[Issers|Isser]] ([[Boumerdès Province|Boumerdès]]) in his ranks. Indeed, the coach would have watched the first leg of the CAF Confederation Cup final between USMA and [[Young Africans S.C.|Young Africans]], He would then have given the green light to the management of the Qatari club to try this summer.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://africafoot.com/belaid-et-mahious-se-rapprochent-encore-plus-du-qatar/ |title=Belaïd et Mahious se rapprochent encore plus du Qatar |website=africafoot.com |date=30 May 2023 |access-date=30 June 2023}}</ref>

On 3 June 2023, Belaïd won the first title in his football career by winning the [[2022–23 CAF Confederation Cup]] after defeating [[Young Africans S.C.|Young Africans]] of Tanzania.<ref name="barrons.com">{{cite web |url=https://www.barrons.com/news/usm-alger-lift-caf-cup-despite-home-loss-to-young-africans-2cdf88d4 |title=USM Alger Lift CAF Cup Despite Home Loss To Young Africans |website=barrons.com |date=3 June 2023 |access-date=4 June 2023}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.dzfoot.com/football-en-algerie/caf-cc-lusma-remporte-la-coupe-243005.html |title=CAF CC : L'USMA REMPORTE LA COUPE! |website=dzfoot.com |date=3 June 2023 |access-date=4 June 2023}}</ref> On 17 August 2023, Belaïd has finally extended her contract for two years. Many clubs contacted USM Alger captain during this transfer period, as the Belgian club [[Sint-Truidense V.V.|Sint-Truiden]] made an official offer for the player, but the latter rejected it in the end.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.dzfoot.com/football-en-algerie/usm-alger-zinedine-belaid-prolonge-son-contrat-jusqua-2026-246162.html |title=USM Alger : Zinedine Belaid prolonge son contrat jusqu'en 2026 |website= DZfoot |date=17 August 2023 |access-date=1 January 2024}}</ref> On 15 September 2023, Belaïd led USM Alger to win the [[2023 CAF Super Cup|CAF Super Cup]] against [[Al Ahly SC|Al Ahly]] by scoring the only goal in the match, winning the second title in three months.<ref name="lusma-remporte-la-supercoupe-de-la-caf-face-au-ahly">{{cite web |url=https://mediafootdz.dz/lusma-remporte-la-supercoupe-de-la-caf-face-au-ahly/ |title=L'USMA remporte la Supercoupe de la CAF face au Ahly |website=mediafootdz.dz |date=15 September 2023 |access-date=15 September 2023}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://english.ahram.org.eg/News/508470.aspx |title=USM Alger deserved African Super Cup win over Ahly: Coach Benchikha |publisher=ahram.org |date=16 September 2023 }}</ref> Despite renewing his contract with USMA, Belaïd still has ambitions to professionalize in Europe. On 23 June 2024, Zineddine Belaïd met with the Chairman of the Board of Directors of USM Alger Athmane Sehbane, where he agreed that he would officially leave. The team’s management finally agreed not to put obstacles in the way of the player’s ambition and in a way that preserves the rights of the club. The agreement was finally concluded to fulfill the desire of Belaïd to join the Belgian club [[Sint-Truidense V.V.|Sint-Truiden]] and signed his exit paper.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://lagazettedufennec.com/mercato-le-transfert-de-zinedine-belaid-rapporte-un-pactole-a-lusma/ |title=Mercato: Le transfert de Zineddine Belaid rapporte un pactole à l'USMA |website=La gazette du fennec |date=23 June 2024 |access-date=23 June 2024}}</ref>

On 23 August 2025, Belaïd signed a three-year contract with [[JS Kabylie]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.horizons.dz/?p=336917|title= JS Kabylie : Belaïd engagé pour 3 ans |website= horizons |date=23 August 2025 |access-date=23 August 2025}}</ref>

==International career==
In June 2021, Zineddine Belaïd was called up by [[Madjid Bougherra]] for the first time to the [[Algeria A' national football team|Algeria A' national team]] against [[Liberia national football team|Liberia]] to inaugurate the [[Olympic Stadium (Oran)|new stadium]] in Oran in 5–1 victory.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.radioalgerie.dz/news/fr/article/20210617/213444.html |title=Football - Amical : victoire de l'Algérie A' devant le Liberia (5-1) |website=radioalgerie.dz |date= 17 June 2021 |accessdate= 29 August 2021}}</ref> On 2 January 2023, Belaïd was selected for the 28-man squad to participate in the [[2022 African Nations Championship]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.dzfoot.com/equipes-nationales/chan-2022-la-liste-des-28-algeriens-devoilee-236402.html |title=CHAN 2022 : La liste des 28 algériens dévoilée |website=dzfoot.com |date=3 January 2023 |access-date=4 January 2023}}</ref> Belaïd played all the matches reaching the [[2022 African Nations Championship final|final]], settling for runner-up after the defeat against [[Senegal national football team|Senegal]].<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.cafonline.com/total-african-nations-championship/2022/news/senegal-defeat-hosts-algeria-on-penalties-to-win-chan
|title=Senegal win penalty shootout against Algeria to become CHAN champions|date=4 February 2023|work=Cafonline.com|accessdate=22 February 2023}}</ref> On 30 May 2023 the [[Algerian Football Federation|FAF]] publish the list of [[Djamel Belmadi]] for the two matches of the month of June, Where is called Belaïd for the first time and his first match was against [[Uganda national football team|Uganda]] in the [[2023 Africa Cup of Nations qualification Group F|Africa Cup of Nations qualification]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.dzfoot.com/equipes-nationales/en-la-liste-de-belmadi-contre-louganda-et-la-tunisie-242811.html |title=EN : La liste de Belmadi contre l'Ouganda et la Tunisie |website=dzfoot.com |date=30 May 2023 |access-date=21 June 2023}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://lagazettedufennec.com/belaid-si-pas-maintenant-cest-quand/ |title=Zineddine Belaïd, si pas maintenant c'est quand ? |website=Lagazette du fennec |date=7 October 2023 |access-date=31 December 2023}}</ref> On 29 December 2023, Belaïd was named by [[Djamel Belmadi]] to Algeria's 26-man squad for the [[2023 Africa Cup of Nations]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.dzfoot.com/equipes-nationales/officiel-la-liste-des-verts-pour-la-can-est-parue-252031.html |title=Officiel : La liste des Verts pour la CAN est parue ! |website=DZfoot |date=29 December 2023 |access-date=30 December 2023}}</ref>

